{"id":"821","name":"Vehicle Sharing Suite","tagline":"Manage, share and keep track of the status of your vehicle's availability, parking and whereabouts.","icon":"ios12 c255 g59452","latest":"1879","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>A collection of five tools intended for people that share a vehicle with other family members or friends. It uses a shared Apple calendar to manage and keep track of the status of your vehicle's availability, parking and whereabouts.  It makes it a breeze to coordinate the use of the vehicle with others, avoid parking tickets, and find where the vehicle is currently parked.</p>\n<h5>\"Book the Car\"</h5>\n<p>Makes reservations for your vehicle, while checking for booking conflicts.</p>\n<h5>\"I’m Taking the Car\"</h5>\n<p>Creates an event stating that you currently have the vehicle, along with your destination and how long you’ll have it.  If you have a reservation, it will fill out most of the details for you and replace the reservation.</p>\n<h5>\"I Parked the Car\"</h5>\n<p>Logs where you parked the vehicle, along with when the spot is good until.  You’ll get an alert to remind you to move the vehicle.  This will trim any active event for whomever currently has the vehicle.</p>\n<h5>\"Car Status\"</h5>\n<p>Provides a quick status report of the vehicle's current availability, parking and whereabouts.</p>\n<h5>\"Where’s the Car\"</h5>\n<p>Pulls up quick walking directions to the vehicle’s current location - if parked.</p>\n<p>—————</p>\n<p><strong>FEATURES:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Countless different responses from Siri</strong> - <em>sometimes she can be a bit snarky</em></li>\n<li><strong>Optional ‘Quiet Mode’</strong> - <em>can be set for each tool individually</em></li>\n<li><strong>Say day/time or duration</strong> - <em>ie: “Thursday at 8 PM” or “Two days and four hours”</em></li>\n<li><strong>Add notes to each event</strong> - <em>by simply saying “note” followed by your comments</em></li>\n<li><strong>Specify garage parking</strong> - <em>for when you’re not parked on the street</em></li>\n<li><strong>Always have the latest version</strong> - <em>by installing the UpdateKit shortcut!</em>  </li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>and much more...</em></p>\n<p>—————</p>\n<p>The installer will install six shortcuts in total (5 tools + 1 prefs shortcut).</p>\n<p>All instructions are in the top comment of each shortcut.  Read through each of them to learn about all the features and capabilities.</p>\n<p>I hope you find this useful. You can hit me up with questions, comments, bugs or suggestions here or on Reddit at <a href=\"reddit.com/u/opticsugar\">u/OpticSugar</a></p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0.5 - Nov. 9, 2018, 8:43 p.m.</strong></p>"}